track_notes: This track shows the drive rout to the TH and then the hike

This follows a trek that has already been established, but excludes the drive to the trailhead. 

This activation can be done in unison with Squaw Peak (if you have a high-clearance vehicle). 

There is no established trail and the bush-whacking comes with working your way through stepping through small boulders. The hike up the final summit is a steep climb, but worth the views. Up top there is a clearing area where you can establish a variety of antenna configurations.

My route was nearly identical to those already posted, except it went up over the intermediate summit.  Due to the rocky terrain this is a bushwhack that requires careful attention to footing the entire way.
